# Go workspace file — local-dev ergonomics only (open rara-core + rara-addon + an app together).
# NEVER committed: each module couples to rara-addon via a `replace` directive in its own go.mod,
# so it builds standalone in CI (cd rara-X && go test) and in the P2 Docker build. A committed
# go.work would force every sibling module into the workspace and break `cd rara-X && go test`.
go.work
go.work.sum

# Runtime logs (distill/ollama experiments)
*.log
run_*.log

# Personal ops runbook — local-only, never committed. Contains live infra topology
# (tailnet IPs, SA emails, Cloud Run URLs). Stays on the operator's machine only.
# Narrow on purpose: does NOT match the committed *.pt-BR.md design docs nor rara-*/deploy/RUNBOOK.md.
RUNBOOK-OPS-*.pt-BR.md
